File: Gauteng has overtaken Western Cape as the province with the highest numbers of cases cumulatively. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng has become the new epicentre of the coronavirus. The province has overtaken Western Cape as the province with the highest numbers of cases cumulatively. The province recorded more than 75,000 infections. READ: COVID-19: Mass gravesites prepared in Gauteng There were just over 9,000 new cases in the past 24 hours bringing the total to just over 224,000. There have been 3,600 deaths and almost 107,000 recoveries. Just under two million tests have been conducted. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. Updated #COVID19 statistics in SA as at 08 July 2020. pic.twitter.com/XffRlIWmWZ